cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.CV 

The paper presents a neural network architecture that learns algorithms from input-output examples using reinforcement learning. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The architecture uses a neural controller that interacts with an input tape, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks. The use of self-attention and parallel history tape suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE) in the architecture.
